{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I'm just going to play a brief video clip."}]},{"cues":[{"time":6000,"text":"Video:"},{"time":7000,"text":"On the fifth of December 1985, a bottle of 1787 Lafitte was sold"},{"time":13000,"text":"for 105,000 pounds -- nine times the previous world record."},{"time":18000,"text":"The buyer"},{"time":20000,"text":"was Kip Forbes,"},{"time":22000,"text":"son of one of the most flamboyant millionaires of the 20th century."},{"time":25000,"text":"The original owner of the bottle turned out to be"},{"time":27000,"text":"one of the most enthusiastic wine buffs of the 18th century."},{"time":31000,"text":"Ch√¢teau Lafitte is one of the greatest wines in the world,"},{"time":35000,"text":"the prince of any wine cellar."}]},{"cues":[{"time":37000,"text":"Benjamin Wallace: Now, that's about all the videotape that remains of an event"},{"time":39000,"text":"that set off the longest-running mystery in the modern wine world."},{"time":43000,"text":"And the mystery existed because of a gentleman named Hardy Rodenstock."},{"time":48000,"text":"In 1985, he announced to his friends in the wine world"},{"time":51000,"text":"that he had made this incredible discovery."},{"time":53000,"text":"Some workmen in Paris had broken through a brick wall,"},{"time":57000,"text":"and happened upon this hidden cache of wines --"},{"time":60000,"text":"apparently the property of Thomas Jefferson. 1787, 1784."},{"time":65000,"text":"He wouldn't reveal the exact number of bottles,"},{"time":67000,"text":"he would not reveal\nexactly where the building was"},{"time":70000,"text":"and he would not reveal exactly who owned the building."},{"time":73000,"text":"The mystery persisted for about 20 years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":76000,"text":"It finally began to get resolved in 2005 because of this guy.\n"},{"time":81000,"text":"Bill Koch is a Florida billionaire who owns four of the Jefferson bottles,"},{"time":84000,"text":"and he became suspicious."},{"time":86000,"text":"And he ended up spending over a million dollars and hiring ex-FBI"},{"time":90000,"text":"and ex-Scotland Yard agents to try to get to the bottom of this."},{"time":94000,"text":"There's now ample evidence that Hardy Rodenstock is a con man,"},{"time":97000,"text":"and that the Jefferson bottles were fakes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":99000,"text":"But for those 20 years,"},{"time":101000,"text":"an unbelievable number of really eminent and accomplished figures"},{"time":107000,"text":"in the wine world were sort of drawn into the orbit of these bottles."},{"time":109000,"text":"I think they wanted to believe that the most expensive bottle of wine"},{"time":114000,"text":"in the world must be the best bottle of wine in the world,"},{"time":117000,"text":"must be the rarest bottle of wine in the world."},{"time":120000,"text":"I became increasingly, kind of voyeuristically interested in the question of"},{"time":125000,"text":"you know, why do people spend these crazy amounts of money,"},{"time":128000,"text":"not only on wine but on lots of things,"},{"time":131000,"text":"and are they living a better life than me?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":133000,"text":"So, I decided to embark on a quest. \n\n"},{"time":135000,"text":"With the generous backing of a magazine I write for sometimes,"},{"time":138000,"text":"I decided to sample the very best, or most expensive, or most coveted item"},{"time":145000,"text":"in about a dozen categories,"},{"time":147000,"text":"which was a very grueling quest, \nas you can imagine."}]},{"cues":[{"time":149000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":150000,"text":"This was the first one."},{"time":152000,"text":"A lot of the Kobe beef that you see in the U.S. is not the real thing."},{"time":155000,"text":"It may come from Wagyu cattle,"},{"time":157000,"text":"but it's not from the original, Appalachian Hyogo Prefecture in Japan."},{"time":160000,"text":"There are very few places in the U.S. where you can try real Kobe,"},{"time":163000,"text":"and one of them is Wolfgang Puck's restaurant, Cut, in Los Angeles."},{"time":167000,"text":"I went there, and I ordered the eight-ounce rib eye for 160 dollars."},{"time":171000,"text":"And it arrived, and it was tiny. \n\n"},{"time":173000,"text":"And I was outraged."},{"time":175000,"text":"It was like, 160 dollars for this?"},{"time":177000,"text":"And then I took a bite,"},{"time":179000,"text":"and I wished that it was tinier, because Kobe beef is so rich."},{"time":183000,"text":"It's like foie gras -- it's not even like steak."},{"time":186000,"text":"I almost couldn't finish it."},{"time":188000,"text":"I was really happy when I was done."}]},{"cues":[{"time":190000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":191000,"text":"Now, the photographer who took the pictures for this project"},{"time":195000,"text":"for some reason posed his dog in a lot of them,"},{"time":197000,"text":"so that's why you're going to see this recurring character."},{"time":200000,"text":"Which, I guess, you know, communicates to you"},{"time":202000,"text":"that I did not think that one was really worth the price."}]},{"cues":[{"time":206000,"text":"White truffles. \n"},{"time":208000,"text":"One of the most expensive luxury foods by weight in the world."},{"time":210000,"text":"To try this, I went to a Mario Batali restaurant"},{"time":212000,"text":"in Manhattan -- Del Posto."},{"time":214000,"text":"The waiter, you know, came out with the white truffle knob"},{"time":217000,"text":"and his shaver, and he shaved it onto my pasta and he said, you know,"},{"time":221000,"text":"\"Would Signore like the truffles?\""},{"time":223000,"text":"And the charm of white truffles is in their aroma."},{"time":225000,"text":"It's not in their taste, really. It's not in their texture."},{"time":228000,"text":"It's in the smell."},{"time":229000,"text":"These white pearlescent flakes hit the noodles,"},{"time":231000,"text":"this haunting, wonderful, nutty, mushroomy smell wafted up."},{"time":236000,"text":"10 seconds passed and it was gone."},{"time":238000,"text":"And then I was left with these little ugly flakes on my pasta that,"},{"time":242000,"text":"you know, their purpose had been served,"},{"time":245000,"text":"and so I'm afraid to say that this was also a disappointment to me."},{"time":248000,"text":"There were several -- several of these items were disappointments."}]},{"cues":[{"time":252000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":256000,"text":"Yeah.\n\n"},{"time":257000,"text":"The magazine wouldn't pay for me to go there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":259000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":261000,"text":"They did give me a tour, though."},{"time":263000,"text":"And this hotel suite is 4,300 square feet."},{"time":266000,"text":"It has 360-degree views."},{"time":268000,"text":"It has four balconies."},{"time":270000,"text":"It was designed by the architect I.M. Pei."},{"time":272000,"text":"It comes with its own Rolls Royce and driver."},{"time":274000,"text":"It comes with its own wine cellar that you can draw freely from."},{"time":277000,"text":"When I took the tour, it actually included some Opus One, I was glad to see."},{"time":281000,"text":"30,000 dollars for a night in a hotel."}]},{"cues":[{"time":285000,"text":"This is soap that's made from silver nanoparticles,"},{"time":289000,"text":"which have antibacterial properties."},{"time":292000,"text":"I washed my face with this this morning in preparation for this."},{"time":295000,"text":"And it, you know, tickled a little bit and it smelled good,"},{"time":299000,"text":"but I have to say that nobody here"},{"time":301000,"text":"has complimented me on the cleanliness of my face today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":303000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":304000,"text":"But then again, nobody has complimented me on the jeans I'm wearing."},{"time":310000,"text":"These ones GQ did spring for -- I own these -- but I will tell you, \n\n"},{"time":314000,"text":"not only did I not get a compliment from any of you,"},{"time":316000,"text":"I have not gotten a compliment from anybody \n"},{"time":318000,"text":"in the months that I have owned and worn these."},{"time":320000,"text":"I don't think that whether or not you're getting a compliment"},{"time":322000,"text":"should be the test of something's value,"},{"time":324000,"text":"but I think in the case of a fashion item, an article of clothing,"},{"time":327000,"text":"that's a reasonable benchmark."},{"time":329000,"text":"That said, a lot of work goes into these."},{"time":331000,"text":"They are made from handpicked organic Zimbabwean cotton"},{"time":335000,"text":"that has been shuttle loomed"},{"time":338000,"text":"and then hand-dipped in natural indigo 24 times."},{"time":342000,"text":"But no compliments."}]},{"cues":[{"time":343000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":344000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":348000,"text":"Armando Manni is a former filmmaker who makes this olive oil"},{"time":350000,"text":"from an olive that grows on a single slope in Tuscany."},{"time":354000,"text":"And he goes to great lengths to protect the olive oil from oxygen and light."},{"time":359000,"text":"He uses tiny bottles, the glass is tinted,"},{"time":362000,"text":"he tops the olive oil off with an inert gas."},{"time":366000,"text":"And he actually -- once he releases a batch of it,"},{"time":369000,"text":"he regularly conducts molecular analyses and posts the results online,"},{"time":374000,"text":"so you can go online and look at your batch number"},{"time":376000,"text":"and see how the phenolics are developing,\n"},{"time":378000,"text":"and, you know, gauge its freshness."},{"time":380000,"text":"I did a blind taste test of this with 20 people and five other olive oils."},{"time":384000,"text":"It tasted fine. It tasted interesting."},{"time":386000,"text":"It was very green, it was very peppery."},{"time":388000,"text":"But in the blind taste test, it came in last."},{"time":392000,"text":"The olive oil that came in first was actually a bottle of"},{"time":395000,"text":"Whole Foods 365 olive oil which had been oxidizing next to my stove"},{"time":401000,"text":"for six months."}]},{"cues":[{"time":402000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":412000,"text":"A recurring theme is that a lot of these things are from Japan --"},{"time":414000,"text":"you'll start to notice."}]},{"cues":[{"time":415000,"text":"I don't play golf, so I couldn't actually road test these,"},{"time":418000,"text":"but I did interview a guy who owns them."},{"time":420000,"text":"Even the people who market these clubs -- I mean, they'll say"},{"time":423000,"text":"these have four axis shafts which minimize loss of club speed"},{"time":427000,"text":"and thereby drive the ball farther -- but they'll say, look, you know,"},{"time":431000,"text":"you're not getting 57,000 dollars worth of performance from these clubs."},{"time":434000,"text":"You're paying for the bling,"},{"time":436000,"text":"that they're encrusted with gold and platinum."},{"time":438000,"text":"The guy who I interviewed who owns them did say"},{"time":440000,"text":"that he's gotten a lot of pleasure out of them, so ..."}]},{"cues":[{"time":444000,"text":"Oh, yeah, you know this one?"},{"time":446000,"text":"This is a coffee made from a very unusual process."},{"time":452000,"text":"The luwak is an Asian Palm Civet."},{"time":454000,"text":"It's a cat that lives in trees,"},{"time":456000,"text":"and at night it comes down and it prowls the coffee plantations. \n\n"},{"time":460000,"text":"And apparently it's a very picky eater and it, you know,"},{"time":462000,"text":"hones in on only the ripest coffee cherries."},{"time":466000,"text":"And then an enzyme in its digestive tract leeches into the beans,"},{"time":470000,"text":"and people with the unenviable job of collecting these cats' leavings"},{"time":475000,"text":"then go through the forest collecting the, you know, results"},{"time":480000,"text":"and processing it into coffee -- although you actually can buy it"},{"time":484000,"text":"in the unprocessed form."},{"time":488000,"text":"That's right. \n"}]},{"cues":[{"time":490000,"text":"Unrelatedly --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":492000,"text":"(Laughter)\n"}]},{"cues":[{"time":494000,"text":"Japan is doing crazy things with toilets."}]},{"cues":[{"time":497000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":504000,"text":"There is now a toilet that has an MP3 player in it."},{"time":507000,"text":"There's one with a fragrance dispenser."},{"time":509000,"text":"There's one that actually analyzes the contents of the bowl"},{"time":513000,"text":"and transmits the results via email to your doctor."},{"time":517000,"text":"It's almost like a home medical center -- \n"},{"time":519000,"text":"and that is the direction that Japanese toilet technology is heading in."},{"time":523000,"text":"This one does not have those bells and whistles,"},{"time":525000,"text":"but for pure functionality it's pretty much the best -- the Neorest 600."},{"time":529000,"text":"And to try this -- I couldn't get a loaner,"},{"time":532000,"text":"but I did go into the Manhattan showroom of the manufacturer, Toto,"},{"time":537000,"text":"and they have a bathroom off of the showroom that you can use, which I used."},{"time":541000,"text":"It's fully automated -- you walk towards it, and the seat lifts."},{"time":544000,"text":"The seat is preheated. \n"},{"time":546000,"text":"There's a water jet that cleans you."},{"time":548000,"text":"There's an air jet that dries you."},{"time":550000,"text":"You get up, it flushes by itself."},{"time":552000,"text":"The lid closes, it self-cleans."},{"time":554000,"text":"Not only is it a technological leap forward,"},{"time":556000,"text":"but I really do believe it's a bit of a cultural leap forward."},{"time":558000,"text":"I mean, a no hands, no toilet paper toilet."},{"time":561000,"text":"And I want to get one of these."}]},{"cues":[{"time":563000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":567000,"text":"This was another one I could not get a loaner of."},{"time":572000,"text":"Tom Cruise supposedly owns this bed."},{"time":574000,"text":"There's a little plaque on the end that, you know,"},{"time":576000,"text":"each buyer gets their name engraved on it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":579000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":585000,"text":"To try this one, the maker of it let me and my wife"},{"time":587000,"text":"spend the night in the Manhattan showroom. \n"},{"time":589000,"text":"Lights glaring in off the street, \n"},{"time":591000,"text":"and we had to hire a security guard and all these things."},{"time":594000,"text":"But anyway, we had a great night's sleep."},{"time":596000,"text":"And you spend a third of your life in bed."},{"time":598000,"text":"I don't think it's that bad of a deal."}]},{"cues":[{"time":601000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":602000,"text":"This was a fun one.\n"},{"time":604000,"text":"This is the fastest street-legal car in the world"},{"time":608000,"text":"and the most expensive production car. \n\n"},{"time":610000,"text":"I got to drive this with a chaperone from the company,"},{"time":612000,"text":"a professional race car driver,"},{"time":614000,"text":"and we drove around the canyons outside of Los Angeles"},{"time":617000,"text":"and down on the Pacific Coast Highway."},{"time":619000,"text":"And, you know, when we pulled up to a stoplight"},{"time":622000,"text":"the people in the adjacent cars kind of gave us respectful nods."},{"time":626000,"text":"And it was really amazing."},{"time":628000,"text":"It was such a smooth ride."},{"time":630000,"text":"Most of the cars that I drive, if I get up to 80 they start to rattle."},{"time":632000,"text":"I switched lanes on the highway and the driver, this chaperone, said,"},{"time":635000,"text":"\"You know, you were just going 110 miles an hour.\""},{"time":637000,"text":"And I had no idea that I was one of those obnoxious people"},{"time":640000,"text":"you occasionally see weaving in and out of traffic,"},{"time":642000,"text":"because it was just that smooth."},{"time":644000,"text":"And if I was a billionaire, I would get one."}]},{"cues":[{"time":646000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":651000,"text":"This is a completely gratuitous video I'm just going to show"},{"time":654000,"text":"of one of the pitfalls of advanced technology."},{"time":656000,"text":"This is Tom Cruise arriving at the \"Mission: Impossible III\" premiere."},{"time":669000,"text":"When he tries to open the door, \n\n"},{"time":671000,"text":"you could call it \"Mission: Impossible IV.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":676000,"text":"There was one object that I could not get my hands on,"},{"time":678000,"text":"and that was the 1947 Cheval Blanc. \n\n"},{"time":680000,"text":"The '47 Cheval Blanc is probably the most mythologized wine of the 20th century."},{"time":684000,"text":"And Cheval Blanc is kind of an unusual wine for Bordeaux"},{"time":687000,"text":"in having a significant percentage of the Cabernet Franc grape."},{"time":691000,"text":"And 1947 was a legendary vintage,"},{"time":694000,"text":"especially in the right bank of Bordeaux."},{"time":696000,"text":"And just together, that vintage and that chateau took on this aura"},{"time":700000,"text":"that eventually kind of gave it this cultish following."},{"time":704000,"text":"But it's 60 years old."},{"time":706000,"text":"There's not much of it left."},{"time":708000,"text":"What there is of it left you don't know if it's real --"},{"time":710000,"text":"it's considered to be the most faked wine in the world."},{"time":712000,"text":"Not that many people are looking to pop open"},{"time":714000,"text":"their one remaining bottle for a journalist."}]},{"cues":[{"time":718000,"text":"So, I'd about given up trying to get my hands on one of these."},{"time":722000,"text":"I'd put out feelers to retailers, to auctioneers,"},{"time":724000,"text":"and it was coming up empty."},{"time":726000,"text":"And then I got an email from a guy named Bipin Desai."},{"time":728000,"text":"Bipin Desai is a U.C. Riverside theoretical physicist"},{"time":732000,"text":"who also happens to be the preeminent organizer of rare wine tastings,"},{"time":736000,"text":"and he said, \"I've got a tasting coming up"},{"time":738000,"text":"where we're going to serve the '47 Cheval Blanc.\""},{"time":740000,"text":"And it was going to be a double vertical --"},{"time":742000,"text":"it was going to be 30 vintages of Cheval Blanc,"},{"time":745000,"text":"and 30 vintages of Yquem."},{"time":747000,"text":"And it was an invitation you do not refuse.\n"},{"time":750000,"text":"I went."}]},{"cues":[{"time":752000,"text":"It was three days, four meals. \n"},{"time":754000,"text":"And at lunch on Saturday, we opened the '47."},{"time":757000,"text":"And you know, it had this fragrant softness,"},{"time":761000,"text":"and it smelled a little bit of linseed oil."},{"time":764000,"text":"And then I tasted it, and it,"},{"time":766000,"text":"you know, had this kind of unctuous, porty richness,"},{"time":770000,"text":"which is characteristic of that wine --"},{"time":772000,"text":"that it sort of resembles port in a lot of ways."},{"time":774000,"text":"There were people at my table who thought it was, you know, fantastic."},{"time":776000,"text":"There were some people who were a little less impressed."},{"time":780000,"text":"And I wasn't that impressed."},{"time":783000,"text":"And I don't -- call my palate a philistine palate --"},{"time":787000,"text":"so it doesn't necessarily mean something that I wasn't impressed,"},{"time":791000,"text":"but I was not the only one there who had that reaction."},{"time":794000,"text":"And it wasn't just to that wine."},{"time":796000,"text":"Any one of the wines served at this tasting,"},{"time":798000,"text":"if I'd been served it at a dinner party, it would have been, you know,"},{"time":801000,"text":"the wine experience of my lifetime, and incredibly memorable."},{"time":804000,"text":"But drinking 60 great wines over three days,"},{"time":807000,"text":"they all just blurred together,"},{"time":809000,"text":"and it became almost a grueling experience."}]},{"cues":[{"time":813000,"text":"And I just wanted to finish by mentioning a very interesting study"},{"time":817000,"text":"which came out earlier this year from some researchers at Stanford and Caltech."},{"time":821000,"text":"And they gave subjects the same wine,"},{"time":825000,"text":"labeled with different price tags."},{"time":827000,"text":"A lot of people, you know,"},{"time":829000,"text":"said that they liked the more expensive wine more --"},{"time":832000,"text":"it was the same wine, but they thought it was a different one"},{"time":834000,"text":"that was more expensive."},{"time":836000,"text":"But what was unexpected was that these researchers did"},{"time":838000,"text":"MRI brain imaging while the people were drinking the wine,"},{"time":841000,"text":"and not only did they say they enjoyed the more expensively labeled wine more --"},{"time":845000,"text":"their brain actually registered as experiencing more pleasure"},{"time":849000,"text":"from the same wine when it was labeled with a higher price tag."}]},{"cues":[{"time":852000,"text":"Thank you.\n\n"}]}]}